. <\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Optionally:<\/span><span> Test the cutting efficiency with a T7 endonuclease assay [13] (<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">see<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;\"> <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Note 25<\/span><span>).<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":114765,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1089822,"guid":"FCDD5DF0398D11EB9E2E698650AB7F60","previous_id":1089821,"previous_guid":"FCC56920398D11EB9E2D698650AB7F60","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"CDCE5A65ED17469BA72DFB9BCDFCCBAA","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"3.4 Genome Editing with CRISPR\/Cas9"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"427DE2A5C2444B84BDE80BF1A2C7415F","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">If homologous recombination of a disease correction or knockin of a reporter is the aim of the gene editing, a donor construct has to be provided in addition to the Cas9-sgRNA vector(s). The tag or the gene for the knockin should be framed by regions of the locus in approximately the same length as the part that is transferred into the gene (such as ~1000 bp for incorporation of an antibiotic resistance with promoter) and provided as a linearized DNA fragment. Alternatively, 5\u201325 bp homology can be used with microhomologymediated end-joining [14].<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":114765,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1089823,"guid":"05C38110398E11EB9E2E698650AB7F60","previous_id":1089822,"previous_guid":"FCDD5DF0398D11EB9E2E698650AB7F60","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"40DF3DA6E1B74E929DB892DE16220FC5